Create and Install Your Package

When you create a data stream in Salesforce, Data Cloud generates a data stream definition in the background.

Data stream definitions connect all your configurations from the primary key to custom fields in a data stream. These definitions showcase what’s included in your package, and you can recreate data streams based on the package definition.

When a package includes a data stream, its mapped data models are also included. The data model mapping is autopopulated to prepare for segmentation.

This process requires a Salesforce developer org to create the package and a subscriber org to install it.

In Data Cloud, click Setup, and select Data Cloud Setup.
Under Tools, select Data Kits.
Click New.
Enter the Data Kit properties.
Add a data stream.
In your developer org, create a data stream bundle.
If needed, map the new data streams to a data model.
(Optional) To verify that the data stream is bringing in the correct data, create a segment.
Create a package with the Package Manager in Setup.

Claim a namespace if you plan to create a managed package.

Include the data stream definitions that you want to package.
Click Upload.
Use the package install URL to install the package.

Installing a package requires admin user permissions.

To deploy the data stream from an installed data kit, create the connection and then go to the Data Stream tab to create the data stream.
Select Installed Data Kits & Packages.
Select the data stream definition from the installed data kit.
To create your data stream, click Deploy.

Your data stream is created and is identical to the one in your package instance.

You can now map the data stream to the data model in this instance.

If the data stream in your package was mapped to data models, they’re mapped automatically.

Repeat these steps for each data stream that you want to deploy from the package.
